a%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%2060%2F40%20portfolio%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20to%20balance%20risk%20and%20%26quot%3Bdecent%26quot%3B%20returns%2C%20Jim%20Paulsen%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20veteran%20said%20the%20economy%20seemed%20to%20be%20entering%20a%20new%20era%20of%20less%20frequent%20recessions.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors%20are%20now%20rewarded%20more%20for%20investing%20in%20stocks%2C%20even%20accounting%20for%20the%20risk%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20time-tested%20investment%20strategy%20might%20be%20obsolete%20given%20the%20recent%20trajectory%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvesting-strategy-60-40-portfolio-alternative-stocks-gold-bonds-cash-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E60%2F40%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20classic%20split%20where%20investors%20allocate%2060%25%20of%20their%20money%20to%20stocks%20and%2040%25%20to%20bonds%20%E2%80%94%20no%20longer%20looks%20like%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20for%20investors%20to%20nab%20a%20decent%20return%20while%20shielding%20themselves%20from%20volatility%2C%20according%20to%20Jim%20Paulsen%2C%20a%20Wall%20Street%20veteran%20and%20the%20former%20chief%20investment%20strategist%20of%20The%20Leuthold%20Group.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20the%20US%20economy%20looks%20like%20it's%20entered%20an%20era%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-oil-price-shock-us-iran-war-economic-impact-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecessions%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20become%20rarer%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investors%20looking%20to%20maximize%20their%20returns%20should%20probably%20load%20up%20more%20on%20stocks%2C%20Paulsen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20appropriate%20'average'%20allocation%20to%20stocks%20should%20be%20higher%20for%20'all'%20investors%20today%20compared%20to%20what%20it%20has%20been%20historically%2C%26quot%3B%20Paulsen%20wrote%20in%20a%20Substack%20post%20on%20Monday.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-stock-market-outlook-us-economy-fiscal-stimulus-ai-investment-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecession%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20has%20probably%20been%20permanently%20lowered%20compared%20to%20its%20propensity%20during%20most%20of%20US%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-investments-investing-strategy-60-40-portfolio-stocks-bonds-bofa-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E60%2F40%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20split%20is%20popular%20among%20investors%20seeking%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecent%26quot%3B%20return%20with%20only%20%26quot%3Bmoderate%26quot%3B%20risk%2C%20Paulsen%20said.%20But%20historically%2C%20the%20portfolio%20has%20underperformed%20relative%20to%20a%20portfolio%20with%20a%20100%25%20allocation%20to%20stocks.%20Since%201926%2C%20the%2060%2F40%20portfolio%20has%20returned%209.5%25%20on%20an%20average%20annualized%20basis%2C%20lower%20than%20the%20expected%2012%25%20return%20on%20a%20100%25%20stock%20portfolio%2C%20Paulsen%20estimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20risk-reward%20profile%20of%20stock%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-buy-bonds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebond%20investing%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20skewed%20even%20more%20favorably%20to%20stocks%20over%20the%20last%20several%20decades%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20was%20in%20a%20recession%2017%25%20of%20the%20time%20from%20the%20years%201940-1990%2C%20Paulsen%20said%2C%20which%20was%20around%20the%20time%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvanguard-investment-outlook-advice-60-40-portfolio-bonds-stocks-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E60%2F40%20portfolio%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20popularized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20comparison%2C%20the%20US%20has%20been%20in%20a%20recession%20just%208%25%20of%20the%20time%20over%20the%20last%2036%20years.%20Barring%20the%20brief%20COVID-19%20recession%2C%20the%20US%20hasn't%20had%20an%20endogenous%20downturn%20for%2017%20years%2C%20Paulsen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20hypothetical%20environment%20where%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20%26quot%3Brecession-less%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20investor%20with%20a%20100%25%20allocation%20allocation%20to%20stocks%20could%20expect%20to%20make%20an%20average%20annualized%20monthly%20return%20of%20around%2017%25%2C%20Paulsen%20estimated.%20That%20compares%20to%20an%2011%25-12%25%20average%20annualized%20return%20for%20the%20typical%2060%2F40%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20implies%20that%20without%20recessions%2C%20every%20incremental%20move%20toward%20stocks%20boosts%20returns%20more%20than%20risks%20compared%20to%20an%20economy%20which%20suffers%20recessions%2C%26quot%3B%20Paulsen%20wrote%2C%20though%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20US%20was%20unlikely%20to%20become%20a%20true%20%26quot%3Brecession-less%26quot%3B%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20following%20a%2060%2F40%20portfolio%20split%20today%20will%20likely%20eat%20into%20long-run%20returns%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20retiree%20today%20%E2%80%94%20given%20that%20recession%20frequency%20has%20been%20cut%20in%20half%20since%201990%20%E2%80%94%20should%20probably%20consider%20an%20average%20mix%20meaningfully%20higher%20than%20the%20'old'%2060%2F40%20convention%2C%26quot%3B%20Paulsen%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2060%2F40%20split%20has%20been%20scrutinized%20more%20frequently%20by%20market%20pros%20over%20the%20last%20several%20years%2C%20particularly%20as%20the%20bull%20market%20has%20raced%20higher%20while%20bonds%20have%20failed%20to%20hedge%20volatility%20in%20stocks.%20In%20the%20few%20years%20leading%20up%20to%202025%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw