https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fworld-at-work%2Fmeta-planning-sweeping-layoffs-ai-costs-mount-2026-03-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%20could%20reportedly%20lay%20off%20a%20fifth%20of%20its%20staff%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20skyrocketing%20AI%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBig%20Tech%20no%20longer%20feels%20as%20safe%20as%20it%20once%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Birgisson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20starting%20to%20see%20more%20candidates%20who%2C%205-10%20years%20ago%2C%20would%20not%20have%20considered%20working%20at%20a%20startup%2C%20but%20are%20now%20more%20open%20to%20it%20because%20there%20isn't%20the%20clear%20divide%20between%20'secure'%20and%20'risky'%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feight-ex-servicenow-salespeople-have-been-poached-by-serval-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773738001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b49d06a96e437d6eb852ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feight-ex-servicenow-salespeople-have-been-poached-by-serval-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20exodus%20shows%20how%20difficult%20it%20can%20be%20for%20tech%20companies%20with%20falling%20valuations%20to%20retain%20talent%20when%20AI%20companies%20come%20calling.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bbergman%40insider.com%20(Ben%20Bergman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feight-ex-servicenow-salespeople-have-been-poached-by-serval-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Fed%20is%20likely%20to%20hold%20rates%20steady%20with%20volatile%20oil%20prices%20and%20poor%20US%20jobs%20performance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b858dfa96e437d6eb8654b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJerome%20Powell%20will%20lead%20his%20second-to-last%20Federal%20Reserve%20meeting%20as%20chair%20this%20week.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20will%20announce%20its%20March%20interest%20rate%20decision%20on%20Wednesday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20likely%20the%20FOMC%20will%20hold%20rates%20steady%2C%20especially%20as%20the%20Iran%20war%20has%20sent%20oil%20markets%20into%20chaos.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Fed%20will%20also%20release%20its%20first%20economic%20projections%20of%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20tumultuous%20few%20weeks%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20and%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20paying%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20bank%20will%20announce%20its%20second%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-meeting-january-interest-rates-jerome-powell-live-updates-2026-01%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest-rate%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%202026%20on%20Wednesday%20afternoon%2C%20with%20CME%20FedWatch%20predicting%20a%20near-total%20chance%20of%20a%20rate%20hold%20based%20on%20market%20moves.%20The%20Fed%20cut%20rates%20three%20times%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202025%2C%20and%20has%20penciled%20in%20at%20least%20one%20rate%20cut%20for%20the%20new%20year.%20For%20consumers%2C%20these%20policy%20decisions%20affect%20inflation%2C%20the%20job%20market%2C%20and%20borrowing%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20March%20meeting%2C%20Fed%20leaders%20will%20consider%20the%20dismal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-february-data-live-updates-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFebruary%20job%20growth%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20steady%20inflation%20rate%20up%20through%20last%20month%2C%20first-quarter%20business%20outlook%2C%20and%20the%20budding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foil-price-trump-signals-end-iran-war-stock-markets-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenergy%20and%20oil%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Iran.%20This%20is%20also%20Jerome%20Powell's%20second-to-last%20meeting%20as%20chair.%20He's%20set%20to%20be%20replaced%20by%20ex-Wall%20Streeter%20and%20Trump%20appointee%20Kevin%20Warsh%20in%20May%20if%20Warsh%20is%20confirmed%20by%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20you%20need%20to%20know%20ahead%20of%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221fa6a54a-9926-4bf0-9118-6d3f9aef0c48%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Fed%20has%20a%20near-total%20chance%20of%20holding%20rates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20likely%20that%20the%20Fed%20will%20take%20a%20conservative%20approach%20to%20monetary%20policy%20in%20March.%20Holding%20rates%20steady%20could%20help%20control%20inflation.%20The%20ongoing%20Iran%20war%20has%20raised%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgas-prices-map-us-states-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprice%20of%20gas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20oil%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that's%20likely%20to%20impact%20everything%20from%20plane%20tickets%20to%20grocery%20costs%20over%20the%20next%20several%20months%20unless%20the%20situation%20improves.%20The%20February%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20released%20March%2011%2C%20increased%202.4%25%20year%20over%20year%2C%20the%20same%20rise%20as%20in%20January.%20However%2C%20this%20figure%20doesn't%20yet%20reflect%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-smart-people-saying-about-inflation-energy-prices-iran-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espike%20in%20energy%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20the%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20data%20predate%20the%20start%20of%20the%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz%20%E2%80%94%20a%20major%20trade%20throughfare%20between%20the%20Persian%20Gulf%20and%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Oman%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20largely%20closed%20by%20Iran's%20leadership%20since%20early%20March.%20The%20move%20is%20cutting%20off%20about%2020%25%20of%20global%20oil%20production%2C%20causing%20market%20volatility.%20Oil%20prices%20recently%20surged%20past%20%24100%20a%20barrel%2C%20and%20while%20they've%20calmed%20slightly%2C%20the%20key%20commodity%20is%20still%20far%20more%20expensive%20than%20it%20was%20before%20the%20war.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Hamrick%2C%20senior%20economic%20analyst%20at%20Bankrate%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20oil%20shock%20%26quot%3Bcreates%20a%20real%20problem%20for%20consumers%20in%20the%20broader%20economy%20at%20a%20time%20when%20affordability%20challenges%20have%20already%20been%20first%20and%20foremost%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20major%20issue%20that%20voters%20and%20consumers%20have%20been%20railing%20against.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOil%20isn't%20the%20only%20commodity%20choked%20off%20by%20the%20closure%20of%20the%20Strait%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-inflation-oil-prices-fertilizer-farmers-iran-war-shipping-hormuz-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehit%20to%20fertilizer%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20soon%20cause%20food%20costs%20to%20rise%20if%20the%20war%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20market%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20showing%20clear%20signs%20of%20weakness.%20The%20disappointing%20February%20jobs%20report%20showed%20that%20US%20lost%2092%2C000%20jobs%20that%20month.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20also%20inched%20up%20to%204.4%25.%20This%20is%20a%20contrast%20from%20January%20growth%20and%20the%20central%20bank's%20optimistic%20employment%20outlook%20at%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-meeting-january-jerome-powell-interest-rates-key-takeaways-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elast%20meeting%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20January%20report%20saw%20a%20really%20stark%20reversal%20from%20the%20slow%20movement%20in%202025%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20expectation%20that%20this%20momentum%20would%20continue%20and%20keep%20pace.%20And%20that%20was%20not%20the%20case%20for%20February%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicole%20Bachaud%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECory%20Stahle%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20advised%20people%20to%20look%20at%20the%20broader%20job%20market%20trend%20after%20the%20US%20got%20one%20good%20January%20report%20and%20a%20bad%20one%20in%20February.%20Still%2C%20as%20Stahle%20pointed%20out%2C%20the%20US%20basically%20hasn't%20created%20jobs%20in%20the%20past%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20will%20also%20release%20its%20quarterly%20economic%20projections%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20offering%20a%20window%20into%20its%20rate%20decisions%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20year.%20With%20a%20recent%20track%20record%20of%20policy%20disagreements%20among%20Fed%20leaders%2C%20it's%20possible%20there%20will%20be%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20predictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22acdb802a-3286-469d-ad39-b31dfafccb7d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20the%20Fed's%20decision%20means%20for%20consumers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20decisions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmortgage-rates-inch-higher-as-housing-activity-picks-up-1035924213%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpact%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20credit%20card%20rates%2C%20auto%20loans%2C%20inflation%2C%20and%20job%20market%20churn%20over%20time.%20Lower%20rates%20may%20juice%20a%20sluggish%20job%20market%2C%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20pushing%20consumer%20prices%20higher.%20Powell%20and%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20will%20weigh%20which%20side%20of%20their%20dual%20mandate%20to%20prioritize.%20The%20bank's%20inflation%20goal%20is%202%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Fed%20holds%20rates%2C%20Americans'%20finances%20will%20remain%20largely%20unchanged.%20Mortgage%2C%20auto%2C%20and%20credit%20rates%20tend%20to%20fluctuate%20alongside%20the%20federal%20funds%2C%20though%20it%20takes%20a%20pattern%20of%20decisions%20before%20interest%20rates%20change%20noticeably%20for%20consumers.%20Businesses%20and%20job%20seekers%20hoping%20for%20cheaper%20borrowing%20and%20a%20hotter%20labor%20market%20might%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell%20said%20at%20the%20last%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20press%20conference%20in%20January%20that%20America's%20economy%20is%20coming%20into%20the%20year%20%26quot%3Bon%20a%20firm%20footing%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20%26quot%3Bpolicy%20is%20not%20on%20a%20preset%20course%2C%20and%20we%20will%20make%20our%20decisions%20on%20a%20meeting-by-meeting%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222404308a-2a3a-4ac6-9296-1acd0cbd554c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELeadership%20changes%20are%20imminent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkevin-warsh-fed-chair-nomination-reactions-economists-business-leaders-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enominated%20Warsh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20former%20bank%20executive%20and%20central%20bank%20governor%2C%20to%20succeed%20Powell%20as%20Fed%20chair.%20Warsh%20has%20a%20reputation%20for%20hawkish%20monetary%20policy%20and%20for%20being%20tough%20on%20inflation%2C%20and%20it's%20unclear%20whether%20he%20will%20follow%20through%20on%20Trump's%20request%20for%20more%20rate%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMatt%20Colyar%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Moody's%20Analytics%2C%20said%20the%20inflation%20story%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20got%20a%20Fed%20chair%20tapped%20because%20he%20got%20the%20job%20because%20of%20his%20stated%20intention%20of%20lowering%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20now%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20an%20inflationary%20shock%20that's%20going%20to%20push%20up%20prices%20with%20no%20real%20clear%20end%20game%20in%20sight%2C%26quot%3B%20Colyar%20said%20about%20the%20oil%20shock%20and%20spillover%20effects%20from%20the%20Iran%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarsh's%20nomination%20is%20shadowed%20by%20tensions%20between%20the%20central%20bank%20and%20the%20White%20House.%20Fed%20Governor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-is-lisa-cook-federal-reserve-governor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELisa%20Cook%3C%2Fa%3E's%20case%20was%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20earlier%20this%20year%20after%20Trump%20accused%20her%20of%20mortgage%20fraud%2C%20which%20her%20legal%20team%20denies.%20Powell%20also%20announced%20in%20January%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20launched%20a%20probe%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20still%20ongoing%20%E2%80%94%20into%20the%20Fed's%20handling%20of%20construction%20at%20its%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20probe%20sparked%20major%20concerns%20about%20political%20pressure%20on%20interest%20rates%20and%20Fed%20independence.%20Last%20week%2C%20federal%20judge%20James%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-tosses-federal-reserve-chair-jerome-powell-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBoasberg%20squashed%20two%20subpoenas%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20DOJ%20as%20part%20of%20the%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20mountain%20of%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20the%20Government%20served%20these%20subpoenas%20on%20the%20Board%20to%20pressure%20its%20Chair%20into%20voting%20for%20lower%20interest%20rates%20or%20resigning%2C%26quot%3B%20Boasberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenators%20from%20across%20the%20aisle%2C%20including%20retiring%20North%20Carolina%20Republican%20Thom%20Tillis%2C%20who%20sits%20on%20the%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Banking%2C%20Housing%2C%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%2C%20have%20signaled%20that%20they%20will%20oppose%20a%20confirmation%20vote%20for%20Warsh%20or%20any%20of%20Trump's%20Fed%20picks%20because%20of%20the%20DOJ%20probe.%20These%20confirmation%20hearings%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20scheduled%2C%20though%20Powell's%20term%20ends%20May%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20hopes%20to%20see%20a%20rate%20cut%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhere%20is%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chairman%2C%20Jerome%20'Too%20Late'%20Powell%2C%20today%3F%26quot%3B%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2F%40realDonaldTrump%2Fposts%2F116217763545289031%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eposted%20on%20March%2012%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BHe%20should%20be%20dropping%20Interest%20Rates%2C%20IMMEDIATELY%2C%20not%20waiting%20for%20the%20next%20meeting!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarch-fed-decision-fomc-powell-hold-rates-us-iran-war-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773737941000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b858fb4d65ec51752a16ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarch-fed-decision-fomc-powell-hold-rates-us-iran-war-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jerome%20Powell%20and%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20will%20make%20its%20March%20interest%20rate%20decision%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20a%20likely%20hold.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarch-fed-decision-fomc-powell-hold-rates-us-iran-war-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Boney%20Kapoor%2C%20Janhvi%20move%20to%20Madras%20HC%20over%20Sridevi's%20Chennai%20property%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773737904000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-129628367%2Cimgsize-48038.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%