%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20despite%20US%20intelligence%20anticipating%20such%20retaliation.%20The%20conflict%2C%20now%20in%20its%20third%20week%2C%20has%20seen%20Iranian%20attacks%20on%20US%20positions%20and%20allied%20infrastructure%2C%20disrupting%20vital%20shipping%20lanes%20like%20the%20Strait%20of%20Hormuz.%20Concerns%20are%20mounting%20over%20the%20war's%20justification%20and%20its%20escalating%20regional%20impact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fgulf-news-iran-war-we-were-shocked-trump-reacts-to-iran-hitting-us-gulf-allies-was-there-prior-warning%2Farticleshow%2F129627153.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fgulf-news-iran-war-we-were-shocked-trump-reacts-to-iran-hitting-us-gulf-allies-was-there-prior-warning%2Famp_articleshow%2F129627153.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fgulf-news-iran-war-we-were-shocked-trump-reacts-to-iran-hitting-us-gulf-allies-was-there-prior-warning%2Famp_articleshow%2F129627153.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Palantir%20guide%20to%20stopping%20World%20War%20III%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alex%20Karp%20photo%20collage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b878d2a7a4f9df67ba6f20%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%3B%20ANDREW%20CABALLERO-REYNOLDS%2FGetty%3B%20Michael%20M.%20Santiago%2FGetty%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20July%2C%20four%20high-ranking%20tech%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20involved%20with%20artificial%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20were%20sworn%20into%20the%20US%20Army%20Reserves%20with%20the%20rank%20of%20lieutenant%20colonel.%20They%20were%20part%20of%20a%20new%20unit%20called%20Detachment%20201%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20Executive%20Innovation%20Corps.%20The%20Pentagon%20has%20introduced%20many%20initiatives%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdefense-tech-vc-funding-rounds-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeepen%20relationships%20with%20Silicon%20Valley%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20making%20officers%20out%20of%20multimillionaire%20executives%20with%20no%20military%20experience%20served%20as%20a%20strong%20symbol%20of%20a%20new%20era%20in%20which%20venture%20capitalists%20and%20technologists%20see%20themselves%20as%20essential%20to%20the%20defense%20of%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tech%20industry%2C%20which%20once%20prided%20itself%20on%20its%20libertarian-%20and%20counterculture-inflected%20antiwar%20ideals%2C%20has%20emphatically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalmer-luckey-america-worlds-gun-store-defense-tech-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ere-enlisted%20in%20the%20American%20military%20project%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Drawn%20by%20patriotism%20and%20lucrative%20government%20contracts%2C%20numerous%20tech%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20from%20established%20giants%20like%20Google%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichael-burry-nasdaq-spacex-ipo-listing-elon-musk-tesla-ndx-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20military-minded%20startups%20in%20Southern%20California%20%E2%80%94%20have%20started%20working%20for%20the%20defense%20establishment%2C%20from%20supplying%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20to%20building%20AI-powered%20drones%20and%20autonomous%20weapons%20to%20be%20used%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Gaza%2C%20and%20Iran.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanduril-palmer-luckey-ai-war-conflict-defense-tech-startups-military-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnduril%2C%20a%20leading%20munitions%20startup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20just%20announced%20a%20Pentagon%20contract%20that%20may%20be%20worth%20up%20to%20%2420%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20company%20has%20driven%20tech's%20transformation%20from%20keyboard%20to%20warrior%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founders-skipping-college-new-dropping-out-palantir-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPalantir%2C%20a%20data%20and%20analytics%20firm%20cofounded%20by%20Peter%20Thiel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20a%20current%20market%20cap%20of%20%24360%20billion.%20Palantir's%20financial%20network%20and%20its%20alumni%20are%20responsible%20for%20bringing%20numerous%20defense-tech%20startups%20into%20being.%20And%20it%20helped%20brush%20away%20the%20tech%20industry's%20reticence%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20war-making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20a%20growing%20canon%20of%20books%20by%20and%20about%20Palantirians%20is%20helping%20to%20crystallize%2C%20and%20proselytize%2C%20tech's%20new%20hawkishness.%20Last%20year%2C%20Karp%20and%20his%20Palantir%20colleague%20Nicholas%20W.%20Zamiska%20published%20%26quot%3BThe%20Technological%20Republic%3A%20Hard%20Power%2C%20Soft%20Belief%2C%20and%20the%20Future%20of%20the%20West%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20outlined%20their%20austere%20vision%20for%20a%20militarized%20republic%20secured%20by%20Silicon%20Valley%20technologies%20and%20led%20by%20highly%20skilled%20engineers.%20Last%20fall%2C%20New%20York%20Times%20Magazine%20contributor%20Michael%20Steinberger%20published%20an%20authorized%20biography%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Philosopher%20in%20the%20Valley%3A%20Alex%20Karp%2C%20Palantir%2C%20and%20the%20Rise%20of%20the%20Surveillance%20State.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20Shyam%20Sankar%2C%20Palantir's%20chief%20technology%20officer%20and%20one%20of%20the%20four%20techies-turned-officers%2C%20has%20published%20%26quot%3BMobilize%3A%20How%20to%20Reboot%20the%20American%20Industrial%20Base%20and%20Stop%20World%20War%20III.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECowritten%20with%20his%20colleague%20Madeline%20Hart%2C%20%26quot%3BMobilize%26quot%3B%20claims%20that%20the%20US%20government%20needs%20to%20urgently%20boost%20military%20production%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20in%20order%20to%20head%20off%20a%20conflict%20with%20China%2C%20which%20the%20authors%20think%20will%20attempt%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalmer-luckey-anduril-china-27-strategy-war-taiwan-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecapture%20Taiwan%20in%202027%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20these%20books%2C%20and%20from%20a%20battery%20of%20public%20statements%20by%20Karp%20and%20his%20cofounders%2C%20a%20distinctive%20worldview%20emerges%20%E2%80%94%20an%20unapologetically%20nationalistic%20attitude%20that%20has%20total%20contempt%20for%20one's%20enemies%20in%20politics%20and%20business%20and%20that%20sees%20constant%2C%20world-rending%20conflict%20in%20our%20future.%20This%20belief%20system%20was%20developed%20by%20a%20group%20of%20people%20who%20exhibit%20a%20profound%20wish%20to%20live%20in%20interesting%20times%2C%20to%20be%20the%20shield%20defending%20America%20in%20a%20world%20of%20constant%20threats.%20You%20might%20call%20it%20Palantirianism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Palantir%20library%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Technological%20Republic%3A%20Hard%20Power%2C%20Soft%20Belief%2C%20and%20the%20Future%20of%20the%20West%2C%26quot%3B%20by%20Alex%20Karp%20and%20Nicholas%20W.%20Zamiska%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Philosopher%20in%20the%20Valley%3A%20Alex%20Karp%2C%20Palantir%2C%20and%20the%20Rise%20of%20the%20Surveillance%20State%2C%26quot%3B%20by%20Michael%20Steinberger%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BMobilize%3A%20How%20to%20Reboot%20the%20American%20Industrial%20Base%20and%20Stop%20World%20War%20III%2C%26quot%3B%20by%20Shyam%20Sankar%20and%20Madeline%20Hart%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBirthed%20from%20the%2020-year-long%20global%20war%20on%20terror%2C%20which%20coincided%20with%20the%20tech%20boom%2C%20Palantirianism%20holds%20that%20America's%20adversaries%20don't%20negotiate%20for%20peace.%20They%20surrender%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20or%2C%20as%20Karp%20has%20said%2C%20they%20will%20be%20too%20%26quot%3Bscared%26quot%3B%20to%20challenge%20the%20US%20in%20the%20first%20place%20because%20they%20fear%20immediate%20destruction.%20Palantirians'%20catchword%20is%20%26quot%3Bdeterrence%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20derived%20not%20from%20fear%20of%20mutual%20nuclear%20annihilation%20or%20diplomacy%20but%20by%20developing%20overwhelming%20AI-based%20firepower.%20%26quot%3BThe%20preconditions%20for%20a%20durable%20peace%20often%20come%20only%20from%20a%20credible%20threat%20of%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Karp%20writes%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Technological%20Republic%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Palantirianism%2C%20the%20military-industrial%20complex%20that%20President%20Dwight%20Eisenhower%20famously%20warned%20about%20is%20good%20for%20the%20world%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20would%20be%20far%20better%20with%20the%20tech%20industry's%20participation%20and%20leadership.%20%26quot%3BEisenhower%20wasn't%20warning%20about%20the%20existence%20of%20the%20military-industrial%20complex%3B%20he%20was%20warning%20about%20its%20potential%20for%20undue%20influence%2C%20a%20distinction%20often%20lost%2C%26quot%3B%20write%20Sankar%20and%20Hart.%20In%20their%20view%2C%20bringing%20together%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20is%20not%20a%20step%20toward%20undue%20influence%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbillionaire-bunker-miami-bezos-tom-brady-ivanka-trump-security-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmerica's%20tech%20billionaires%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20exactly%20what%20the%20country%20requires%3A%20%26quot%3BAmerican%20capitalism%20and%20the%20American%20military%20need%20each%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20write.%20%26quot%3BReuniting%20the%20American%20industrial%20base%2C%20commercial%20and%20defense%2C%20is%20an%20existential%20issue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalantirians%20see%20securing%20American%20military%20hegemony%20as%20the%20national%20priority.%20Karp%2C%20who%20once%20called%20himself%20a%20%26quot%3Bneo-Marxist%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20Democratic%20Party%20supporter%20before%20drifting%20rightward%2C%20told%20his%20biographer%20that%20national%20security%20is%20the%20only%20issue%20that%20matters%20to%20him%2C%20and%20that%20the%20tech%20industry's%20workers%20should%20devote%20themselves%20to%20the%20same.%20%26quot%3BA%20generation%20of%20programmers%20remains%20ready%20to%20dedicate%20their%20working%20lives%20to%20sating%20the%20needs%20of%20capitalist%20culture%2C%20and%20to%20enrich%20itself%2C%20but%20declines%20to%20ask%20more%20fundamental%20questions%20about%20what%20ought%20to%20be%20built%20and%20for%20what%20purpose%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20writes.%20The%20answer%20for%20Karp%2C%20the%20high%20priest%20of%20Palantirianism%2C%20is%20obvious%3A%20What%20ought%20to%20be%20built%20is%20what%20makes%20people%20safer.%20What%20makes%20people%20safer%20is%20empowering%20the%20military%2C%20police%2C%20and%20intelligence%20services.%20That%20is%20his%20vision%20of%20the%20common%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20vision%20is%20now%20transforming%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20the%20military%2C%20and%20how%20we%20look%20at%20national%20security.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20made%20the%20mistake%20of%20allowing%20a%20technocratic%20ruling%20class%20to%20form%20and%20take%20hold%20in%20this%20country%20without%20asking%20for%20anything%20quite%20substantial%20in%20return.%20What%20should%20the%20public%20demand%20for%20abandoning%20the%20threat%20of%20revolt%3F%26quot%3B%20Karp%20writes%2C%20sounding%20like%20the%20Marxist%20of%20his%20youth.%20%26quot%3BFree%20email%20is%20not%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPalantir%20grew%20out%20of%20a%20program%20at%20PayPal%20%E2%80%94%20where%20Thiel%20was%20CEO%20%E2%80%94%20to%20fight%20financial%20fraud%20in%20its%20system.%20The%20company%20itself%20was%20later%20founded%20in%202003%20with%20an%20explicit%20mission%3A%20defending%20the%20West%2C%20which%20its%20founders%20see%20as%20imperiled.%20%26quot%3BA%20moment%20of%20reckoning%20has%20arrived%20for%20the%20West%2C%26quot%3B%20Karp%20writes%20early%20in%20his%20book.%20It's%20not%20always%20clear%20what%20those%20threats%20are%20(or%20even%20what%20constitutes%20%26quot%3Bthe%20West%26quot%3B).%20In%20the%20conservative%20tech%20mogul's%20imaginarium%2C%20wokeness%20and%20DEI%20seem%20to%20be%20as%20dangerous%20to%20the%20American%20public%20as%20a%20revanchist%20Russia.%20Karp%20frequently%20refers%20to%20an%20organized%20%26quot%3Bassault%20on%20religion%2C%26quot%3B%20without%20elaborating%20except%20to%20say%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bleft%20us%20vulnerable%20as%20a%20society.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20seed%20money%20from%20the%20CIA's%20In-Q-Tel%20venture%20capital%20firm%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20agency%20established%20to%20help%20incubate%20national-security%20startups%20%E2%80%94%20Palantir%20slowly%20grew%20to%20become%20the%20go-to%20analytics%20platform%20for%20much%20of%20the%20military%20and%20intelligence%20establishment.%20It%20wasn't%20an%20easy%20ride%3A%20The%20company%20was%20in%20the%20red%20for%20more%20than%2020%20years%2C%20and%20it%20sued%20the%20US%20Army%2C%20claiming%20that%20it%20had%20boxed%20out%20Palantir%20by%20violating%20its%20own%20procurement%20rules.%20Palantir%20won%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20cultivated%20numerous%20government%20and%20military%20insiders%20(who%20were%20sometimes%20given%20its%20software%20for%20free)%2C%20and%20now%20runs%20a%20software%20platform%2C%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-took-over-from-google-on-project-maven-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EProject%20Maven%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that's%20used%20across%20the%20US%20military%20and%20NATO.%20It%20has%20other%20software%20tools%20that%20have%20been%20used%20by%20corporations%2C%20police%20departments%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20the%20federal%20government%20when%20it%20was%20tackling%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Peter%20Thiel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b8bd5ba96e437d6eb86a2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeter%20Thiel%3Cp%3EKiyoshi%20Ota%E2%80%94Bloomberg%2FGetty%20Images%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMaven%20started%20as%20software%20to%20analyze%20drone%20video%20feeds%2C%20with%20a%20%2410%20million%20contract%20going%20to%20Google.%20After%20Google%20employees%20protested%20working%20for%20the%20Pentagon%20and%20Google%20dropped%20the%20project%2C%20Palantir%2C%20working%20alongside%20other%20tech%20companies%2C%20picked%20it%20up%20and%20ran%20with%20it.%20Maven%20eventually%20became%20%26quot%3Ban%20all-purpose%20AI%20operating%20system%26quot%3B%20integrating%20vast%20data%20sources%20into%20a%20dashboard%20that%20intelligence%20analysts%20have%20said%20makes%20their%20work%20much%20easier%2C%20even%20saving%20lives%20in%20the%20field.%20Maven%20is%20now%20used%20in%20conjunction%20with%20other%20systems%2C%20such%20as%20Anthropic's%20Claude%20chatbot%2C%20which%20sits%20on%20top%20of%20Palantir's%20platform.%20The%20Washington%20Post%20reported%20that%20Claude%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2026%2F03%2F04%2Fanthropic-ai-iran-campaign%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eused%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20rapidly%20generate%20thousands%20of%20targets%20for%20the%20ongoing%20US-Israeli%20bombing%20campaign%20in%20Iran.%20The%20US%20military%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F03%2F11%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Firan-school-missile-strike.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigating%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20AI%20was%20used%20to%20target%20the%20bombing%20of%20a%20school%20that%20killed%20at%20least%20100%20Iranian%20children.%20In%20a%20sign%20of%20how%20Maven%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20take%20humans%20out%20of%20the%20loop%2C%20Sankar%20and%20Hart%20note%20in%20their%20book%20that%20%26quot%3Bmachine-to-machine%20connections%20were%20enabled%20to%20allow%20Maven%20to%20communicate%20with%20weapons%20systems%20and%20send%20confirmed%20targets%20directly%20to%20artillery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20martial%20mission%2C%20Palantir%20isn't%20like%20many%20software%20companies.%20Most%20employees%20have%20one%20of%20three%20job%20titles%3A%20deployment%20strategist%2C%20product%20development%20engineer%2C%20or%20forward-deployed%20engineer.%20The%20latter%20group%20is%20software%20engineers%20sent%20to%20work%20directly%20with%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20in%20Manhattan%20or%20Kabul%20%E2%80%94%20to%20customize%20Palantir's%20tools%20and%20troubleshoot%20on%20the%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20this%20motley%20%26quot%3Bartists%20colony%26quot%3B%20is%20Karp%2C%20who%20has%20a%20Ph.D.%20from%20Goethe%20University%2C%20enjoys%20cross-country%20skiing%20with%20his%20Norwegian%20ex-commando%20bodyguards%2C%20practices%20tai%20chi%2C%20and%20retains%20four%20Austrian%20assistants%20with%20whom%20he%20speaks%20in%20German.%20An%20ex-Israeli%20intelligence%20officer%20serves%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20kind%20of%20fixer%26quot%3B%20for%20Karp%2C%20who%20describes%20to%20his%20biographer%20a%20lifelong%20feeling%20of%20personal%20vulnerability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarp%20once%20had%20a%20policy%20of%20never%20spending%20more%20than%20%241%20million%20for%20a%20home%3B%20that%20was%20before%20he%20received%20a%20%241.1%20billion%20pay%20package%20in%202020.%20Now%20he%20owns%20a%20private%20jet%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-billionaire-alex-karp-ties-miami-mansion-purchase-hq-move-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elavish%20properties%20all%20over%20the%20country%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20most%20of%20them%20in%20ski%20areas.%20Recently%2C%20he%20spent%20%24120%20million%20on%20a%20Benedictine%20monastery%20in%20Colorado.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20calls%20himself%20%26quot%3Ba%20fluorescent%20praying%20mantis.%26quot%3B%20With%20his%20many-limbed%20mannerisms%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-karp-ai-job-displacement-humanities-democratic-voters-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebraggadocious%20quips%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Karp%20has%20turned%20himself%20into%20a%20mascot%20for%20Palantir's%20culture.%20%26quot%3BAlways%20energetic%20and%20upbeat%20around%20the%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20he's%20known%20for%20launching%20into%20impromptu%20talks%20with%20employees%20that%20become%20an%20%26quot%3Borgy%20of%20free%20association%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinberger%20writes.%20He%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20little%20bit%20incoherent%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20also%20exhibits%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20charisma.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20public%2C%20his%20mad-mogul%20image%20can%20play%20well%2C%20generating%20viral%20clips%20of%20his%20vows%20to%20drone%20enemies%20with%20%26quot%3Bfentanyl-laced%20urine.%26quot%3B%20TV%20producers%20began%20to%20love%20him%20because%20%26quot%3Bhe%20was%20reliably%20unfiltered%2C%20thanks%20in%20part%20to%20his%20practice%20of%20getting%20hopped-up%20on%20Mexican%20Coke%20beforehand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20son%20of%20a%20white%20Jewish%20father%20and%20a%20Black%20mother%2C%20Karp's%20identity%20has%20been%20a%20core%20throughline%20in%20his%20life%20and%20career.%20As%20a%20child%2C%20Karp%20was%20bullied%20at%20school%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20sense%20of%20fear%20and%20personal%20instability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20a%20racially%20amorphous%2C%20far-left%20Jewish%20kid%20who's%20also%20dyslexic%20%E2%80%94%20would%20you%20not%20come%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20you're%20fucked%3F%26quot%3B%20Karp%20says%20to%20Steinberger.%20In%20this%20context%2C%20Karp's%20sense%20of%20identity%20was%20hopelessly%20complicated%20and%20a%20potential%20social%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarp%20didn't%20tell%20his%20Palantir%20colleagues%20that%20he%20was%20Black%20until%202019%2C%20but%20he%20presented%20differently%20in%20his%20youth.%20He%20went%20to%20college%20at%20Haverford%2C%20where%20he%20%26quot%3Bwas%20active%20in%20black%20student%20affairs%2C%20and%20his%20social%20life%20mainly%20revolved%20around%20Haverford's%20black%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinberger%20writes.%20He%20organized%20a%20conference%20at%20Yale%20about%20racism%20on%20college%20campuses%20and%20wore%20a%20Palestinian%20keffiyeh%20in%20a%20yearbook%20photo.%20One%20of%20his%20close%20friends%20from%20the%20time%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20much%20more%20of%20a%20Black%20man%20then%20than%20he%20is%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20college%2C%20Karp%20enrolled%20at%20Stanford%20Law%20School%2C%20which%20he%20almost%20immediately%20regarded%20as%20a%20mistake.%20He%20became%20friends%20with%20another%20disenchanted%20classmate%2C%20Thiel%2C%20who%20at%20the%20time%20was%20already%20a%20deeply%20ideological%20veteran%20of%20campus%20culture%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Stanford%2C%20Karp%20moved%20to%20Germany%20to%20pursue%20a%20doctorate%20in%20sociology%20at%20Goethe%20University.%20Karp%20would%20later%20say%20that%20Jurgen%20Habermas%2C%20one%20of%20Germany's%20postwar%20intellectual%20giants%2C%20was%20for%20a%20time%20his%20dissertation%20advisor%2C%20which%20Habermas%20has%20denied.%20According%20to%20letters%20examined%20by%20Steinberger%2C%20Habermas%20tried%20to%20steer%20Karp%20toward%20an%20English-language%20degree%20in%20another%20subject.%20%26quot%3BYour%20topic%20would%20require%20a%20literary%20approach%20to%20a%20topic%20that%20often%20overwhelms%20the%20linguistic%20sensibility%20of%20us%20native%20speakers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20yours%2C%20you%20won't%20blame%20me%2C%20even%20more%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Habermas%20wrote%20to%20Karp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKarp%20didn't%20listen.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20finish%20his%20dissertation%20%E2%80%94%20an%20examination%20of%20how%20aggression%20is%20used%20as%20a%20tool%20of%20social%20integration%20%E2%80%94%20which%20he%20wrote%20in%20German%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20Karola%20Brede%2C%20who%20had%20previously%20studied%20under%20Habermas.%20With%20Brede%2C%20Karp%20cowrote%20an%20academic%20article%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20one%20he%20published%20%E2%80%94%20a%20consideration%20of%20%26quot%3Beliminationist%26quot%3B%20anti-Semitism%20and%20Daniel%20Goldhagen's%20book%20%26quot%3BHitler's%20Willing%20Executioners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20since%2C%20Karp%20has%20embraced%20his%20Jewishness%20while%20expressing%20reluctance%20to%20claim%20his%20Black%20identity.%20The%20story%20of%20his%20parents'%20relationship%20became%20for%20him%20a%20kind%20of%20cautionary%20tale%20of%20how%20identity%20politics%20run%20amok.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20father%20wanted%20to%20marry%20a%20Black%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Ben%20Karp%2C%20Alex's%20brother.%20%26quot%3BDating%20Leah%20was%20a%20powerful%20way%20of%20signaling%20his%20progressivism%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinberger%20notes.%20Leah%20Jaynes%20liked%20that%20Bob%20Karp%20was%20Jewish%2C%20and%20Karp%20liked%20that%20she%20was%20Black.%20They%20eventually%20divorced%2C%20after%20which%20Bob%20Karp%20remarried%20and%20adopted%20biracial%20children.%20Bob's%20new%20family%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20his%20sons.%20%26quot%3BAlex's%20realization%2C%20years%20later%2C%20that%20racial%20and%20ethnic%20identity%20had%20been%20foundational%20to%20his%20parents'%20relationship%20was%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20he%20developed%20a%20visceral%20dislike%20of%20identity%20politics%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20Steinberger.%20%26quot%3BHe%20felt%20as%20if%20he%20had%20been%20the%20product%20of%20virtue%20signaling%2C%20and%20it%20bothered%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteinberger%20depicts%20Karp's%20personal%20reckoning%20over%20his%20parentage%20as%20part%20of%20what%20moved%20him%20to%20the%20right.%20In%202015%2C%20he%20told%20company%20employees%20that%20he%20didn't%20like%20Trump.%20According%20to%20%26quot%3BThe%20Philosopher%20in%20the%20Valley%2C%26quot%3B%20Karp%20once%20told%20a%20friend%20that%20he%20wouldn't%20mind%20pushing%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20out%20of%20a%20helicopter.%20The%20company%20has%20gone%20on%20to%20work%20for%20ICE%20and%20other%20government%20agencies%20executing%20hardline%20Trump%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20global%20events%20contributed%20to%20Karp's%20political%20metamorphosis%3A%20COVID%20and%20Hamas'%20attack%20against%20Israel%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%202023.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Karp%20stocked%20up%20on%20canned%20food%20and%20bullets%2C%20and%20loved%20his%20time%20in%20isolation.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20pandemic%20was%20wretched%20for%20most%20people%2C%20Karp%20found%20it%20blissful%2C%26quot%3B%20writes%20Steinberger.%20Plenty%20of%20time%20for%20cross-country%20skiing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Palantir%20returned%20from%20remote%20work%2C%20Karp's%20proclamations%20became%20more%20extreme.%20He%20started%20calling%20Palantir%20%26quot%3Ba%20prepper%20company%26quot%3B%20and%20reveling%20in%20its%20role%20in%20doling%20out%20violence%20to%20enemies%20of%20the%20West.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOct.%207%20reanimated%20Karp's%20sense%20of%20personal%20vulnerability%20and%20his%20commitment%20to%20Israel.%20Having%20once%20celebrated%20the%20virtues%20of%20debate%20with%20his%20friend%20and%20political%20opposite%20Peter%20Thiel%2C%20he%20told%20Palantirians%20that%20the%20company%20wouldn't%20tolerate%20any%20disagreement%20over%20its%20work%20for%20the%20country.%20Palantir%20took%20out%20a%20full%20page%20ad%20in%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20declaring%2C%20%26quot%3BPalantir%20Stands%20With%20Israel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Karp's%20never-apologize-never-explain%20leadership%2C%20Palantir%20has%20become%20a%20leading%20bogeyman%20for%20opponents%20of%20the%20surveillance%20state.%20New%20York%20City%20is%20now%20speckled%20with%20posters%20denouncing%20the%20company%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Benemy.%26quot%3B%20Former%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Robert%20Reich%20recently%20called%20Palantir%20%26quot%3BAmerica's%20most%20dangerous%20corporation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20is%20more%20tangled.%20By%20its%20own%20claim%2C%20Palantir%20proudly%20stands%20for%20American%20militarism%2C%20abets%20the%20surveillance%20state%2C%20and%20has%20catalyzed%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%20toward%20supporting%20the%20security%20services.%20But%20influential%20as%20Palantir%20is%2C%20the%20company%20makes%20software%20%E2%80%94%20tools%20to%20implement%20government%20policy.%20It%20does%20not%20directly%20collect%20data%20or%20conduct%20surveillance.%20It%20sucks%20up%20that%20information%20from%20clients%2C%20including%20authoritarian%20states%2C%20making%20the%20job%20of%20war-making%20or%20repression%20potentially%20much%20easier.%20There%20are%20numerous%20firms%20beyond%20Palantir%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20big%20five%20%26quot%3Bprime%26quot%3B%20defense%20contractors%20%E2%80%94%20engaged%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPalantirianism%20%E2%80%94%20a%20belief%20system%20that%20is%20now%20being%20spread%20through%20venture%20capital%20investments%20in%20startups%20like%20Anduril%2C%20Saronic%2C%20and%20Shield%20AI%2C%20and%20tech's%20close%20alliance%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration%20%E2%80%94%20is%20far%20more%20influential%20than%20Palantir%20itself.%20People%20%26quot%3Bwant%20to%20know%20they%20are%20safe%2C%20and%20safe%20means%20that%20the%20other%20person%20is%20scared%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fgaza-war-trump-silicon-valley-military%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKarp%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20at%20an%20appearance%20at%20the%20Ronald%20Reagan%20Defense%20Forum.%20This%20is%20the%20simple%20core%20belief%20that%20now%20animates%20the%20defense%20tech%20industry%20and%20swaths%20of%20the%20Silicon%20Valley%20elite.%20(Elon%20Musk%20is%20a%20Karp%20fan.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202025%2C%20Karp%20was%20writing%20in%20shareholder%20letters%20that%20the%20West%20owed%20its%20success%20to%20its%20primacy%20at%20%26quot%3Bapplying%20organized%20violence%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20notion%20of%20which%20he%20evidently%20approved.%20He%20started%20talking%20about%20how%20certain%20cultures%20were%20%26quot%3Bregressive%20and%20harmful%26quot%3B%20compared%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20been%20building%20products%20for%20a%20world%20that%20is%20violent%2C%20disjointed%2C%20and%20irrational%2C%20a%20world%20in%20which%20you%20have%20to%20show%20strength%2C%26quot%3B%20Karp%20said%20during%20an%20earnings%20call.%20People%20%26quot%3Bhave%20to%20pick%20sides.%26quot%3B%20Some%20people%20%26quot%3Bare%20violent%20and%20not%20conformant%20with%20morality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20years%2C%20Karp%20said%20that%20fascism%20was%20his%20greatest%20fear.%20He%20wanted%20nothing%20more%20than%20to%20stem%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20far%20right%20in%20America.%20Yet%20Karp's%20company%20has%20provided%20direct%20assistance%20to%20what%20many%20observers%20have%20described%20as%20the%20most%20authoritarian%20president%20in%20US%20history.%20He%20did%20all%20this%20with%20the%20help%20of%20his%20close%20friend%20Peter%20Thiel%2C%20Palantir's%20chairman%2C%20an%20early%20Trump%20supporter%20who%20decades%20ago%20said%20that%20he%20had%20tired%20of%20electoral%20democracy.%20Steinberger%20summed%20up%20the%20contradiction%3A%20%26quot%3BWith%20Trump%20restored%20to%20power%2C%20it%20appeared%20that%20authoritarianism%20had%20triumphed%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20that%20Palantir%2C%20which%20Karp%20had%20always%20touted%20as%20a%20bulwark%20of%20the%20liberal%20international%20order%2C%20would%20henceforth%20be%20serving%20the%20agenda%20of%20a%20president%20who%20was%20contemptuous%20of%20America's%20political%20tradition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Karp%20has%20matured%2C%20in%20his%20biographer's%20view%2C%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bstatesman%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20is%20still%20driven%20by%20spleen.%20Throughout%20%26quot%3BThe%20Philosopher%20in%20the%20Valley%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20repeatedly%20complains%20that%20his%20college%20alma%20mater%20hasn't%20invited%20him%20to%20give%20a%20speech%20or%20cultivated%20him%20as%20a%20donor.%20Karp%20seems%20to%20detests%20Haverford%20with%20a%20similar%20passion%20that%20he%20applies%20to%20terrorists%20and%20student%20protesters.%20%26quot%3BI%20eventually%20came%20to%20realize%20that%20he%20needed%20enemies%2C%26quot%3B%20Steinberger%20writes%20of%20Karp.%20That%20need%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20has%20implications%20for%20us%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjacob-silverman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJacob%20Silverman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20contributing%20writer%20for%20Business%20Insider.%20He%20is%20the%20author%2C%20most%20recently%2C%20of%20%26quot%3BGilded%20Rage%3A%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20the%20Radicalization%20of%20Silicon%20Valley.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-guide-stopping-world-war-iii-karp-book-review-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773735061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b878eba96e437d6eb86920%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-guide-stopping-world-war-iii-karp-book-review-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Can%20one%20secretive%20Silicon%20Valley%20giant%20reshape%20how%20we%20fight%